OL,6,FMs Spooner, whose pregnancy sickness
OL,7,Fwas so severe she had to have a
OL,8,Ftermination, warned of inequality in
OL,9,Faccess to treatments. She recalled
OL,10,Fhaving to travel to an abortion clinic
OL,11,Fin Bargoed to get medication, a
OL,12,Fprocess she described as "immensely
OL,13,Fdifficult".
OL,15,FWhile the Welsh Government has
OL,16,Finsisted health boards have discretion
OL,17,Fto prescribe the drug "when other
OL,18,Ftreatments... are ineffective", staff
OL,19,Fand patients report a different
OL,20,Freality.
